Title: Pre Bike Activation
WorkoutDescription: Before setting off to ride your bike carry out the following exercises / mobility exercises to get yourself ready to ride. 1) - Banded Glute Bridge - 2 sets of 10 to 15 holding for 2 seconds at the top. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p7cFEtMC68g 2) - Crab walks - do 10 small steps each way twice, ensure knees and wider than your feet. https://www.youtube.com/shorts/L6Drl4tYXjo 3) - Low lunge with a twist - Do 2 or 3 each side, hold for a few seconds. https://www.youtube.com/shorts/peb887Bc0-Q 4) - Supine heel tap - 10 to 12 taps on each heel. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xxv-9mA3qLc 5) - Leg swings - nice and controlled, around 10 to 12 on each leg. https://www.youtube.com/shorts/ya7xU4Obypg

It has gotten a bit better m this season (I’ve tried to use bunjees, equipment, different sprints etc) but ultimately I still don’t have the necessary speed which is required especially at the start of a race which is why I always have to catch up / swim myself up. I just find it really difficult and cannot seem to swim any faster at the moment. Also for example I know that had I done the 50s max off 60 instead of 90 I would have still gotten the same and the same for the 100s if I would have gone off a slower time than 1.30 I would still have gotten the same times. I’m not sure why I find it so difficult to find speed in swimming or how to improve this, hopefully you can help with this* *07/27/2025 Steve Lloyd: Ok interesting reflections*

Title: Pre Bike Activation
WorkoutDescription: Before setting off to ride your bike carry out the following exercises / mobility exercises to get yourself ready to ride. 1) - Banded Glute Bridge - 2 sets of 10 to 15 holding for 2 seconds at the top. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p7cFEtMC68g 2) - Crab walks - do 10 small steps each way twice, ensure knees and wider than your feet. https://www.youtube.com/shorts/L6Drl4tYXjo 3) - Low lunge with a twist - Do 2 or 3 each side, hold for a few seconds. https://www.youtube.com/shorts/peb887Bc0-Q 4) - Supine heel tap - 10 to 12 taps on each heel. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xxv-9mA3qLc 5) - Leg swings - nice and controlled, around 10 to 12 on each leg. https://www.youtube.com/shorts/ya7xU4Obypg

WorkoutDescription: Before setting off to ride your bike carry out the following exercises / mobility exercises to get yourself ready to ride. 1) - Banded Glute Bridge - 2 sets of 10 to 15 holding for 2 seconds at the top. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p7cFEtMC68g 2) - Crab walks - do 10 small steps each way twice, ensure knees and wider than your feet. https://www.youtube.com/shorts/L6Drl4tYXjo 3) - Low lunge with a twist - Do 2 or 3 each side, hold for a few seconds. https://www.youtube.com/shorts/peb887Bc0-Q 4) - Supine heel tap - 10 to 12 taps on each heel. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xxv-9mA3qLc 5) - Leg swings - nice and controlled, around 10 to 12 on each leg. https://www.youtube.com/shorts/ya7xU4Obypg

WorkoutDescription: Before setting off to ride your bike carry out the following exercises / mobility exercises to get yourself ready to ride. 1) - Banded Glute Bridge - 2 sets of 10 to 15 holding for 2 seconds at the top. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p7cFEtMC68g 2) - Crab walks - do 10 small steps each way twice, ensure knees and wider than your feet. https://www.youtube.com/shorts/L6Drl4tYXjo 3) - Low lunge with a twist - Do 2 or 3 each side, hold for a few seconds. https://www.youtube.com/shorts/peb887Bc0-Q 4) - Supine heel tap - 10 to 12 taps on each heel. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xxv-9mA3qLc 5) - Leg swings - nice and controlled, around 10 to 12 on each leg. https://www.youtube.com/shorts/ya7xU4Obypg
